I need to identify the tangible items held for use in production, supply of goods/services, rental, or administrative purposes on the balance sheet.

Looking at the balance sheet carefully, the item that best represents these tangible assets is "Fixed Assets". Fixed assets are typically property, plant, and equipment used in business operations.

From the balance sheet:
- Initial Fixed Assets value: 8000000.00 (as of 2023-12-31)
- End Fixed Assets value: 8000000.00 (as of 2024-02-01)

Note that while the gross value of fixed assets remains the same, there is accumulated depreciation of 91509.94 at the end date. However, the task asks for the values of the tangible items themselves (not net of depreciation), so I'll use the Fixed Assets line item values.
